Section 1:
1 L.D. 424
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 278, L.D. 424, “An Act Concerning the
10 Concealed Carrying of a Handgun by an Individual Who Is 18 Years of Age but Under 21
11 Years of Age”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act Concerning the Concealed Carrying of a Handgun by an Individual Who Is
14 18 Years of Age or Older but Under 21 Years of Age'
15 Amend the bill by inserting before section 1 the following:
16 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §11212-A, sub-§3, ¶E, as enacted by PL 2017, c. 176, §2, is
17 amended to read:
18 E. A person who is 21 18 years of age or older and is not otherwise prohibited from
19 possessing a firearm or is 18 years of age or older and under 21 years of age and is on
20 active duty in the Armed Forces of the United States or the National Guard or is an
21 honorably discharged veteran of the Armed Forces of the United States or the National
22 Guard and is not otherwise prohibited from carrying a firearm may have in or on a
23 vehicle a loaded pistol or revolver. This paragraph does not include a person who is
24 18 years of age or older, who meets the age requirement for enrollment under Title
25 20-A, section 5201, subsection 1 and who is currently enrolled in a public or private
26 secondary school in the State.'
27 Amend the bill in section 1 in paragraph A-1 in the last line (page 1, line 9 in L.D.) by
28 inserting after the following: "firearm" the following: '. This paragraph does not include a
29 person who is 18 years of age or older, who meets the age requirement for enrollment under
30 Title 20-A, section 5201, subsection 1 and who is currently enrolled in a public or private
31 secondary school in the State'
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR1149(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 278, L.D. 424
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the minority report, clarifies that a person who is 18 years
33 of age or older, who has not reached 20 years of age and who is currently enrolled in a
44 public or private secondary school in the State may not carry a concealed handgun without
55 a valid permit.
66 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
77 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1149(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
